<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT,
        TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Camshaft Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the engine in the vertical position, lubricate the camshaft and the camshaft
                    bushings using clean engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently slide the camshaft assembly into the crankcase. Be careful not to damage the
                    camshaft bushings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the camshaft gear so the bolts can be inserted through the gear access holes into
                    the thrust plate. Tighten each bolt to the specified special torque. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150531">5.31</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align gear train timing marks. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_81.xml" xrefid="ef4150518">5.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check camshaft gear backlash and camshaft end play. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk document="e415_81.xml" xrefid="ef4150519">5.19</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk document="e415_81.xml" xrefid="ef4150520">5.20</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    for procedure. Specifications must be met.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150530" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11083" filename="../figcg1/cg11083.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.30 Checking Push Rod for Straightness.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150531" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12091" filename="../figcg1/cg12091.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.31 Tighten Camshaft Bolts.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tappets</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the tappets with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve or roller tappets and guides into their original bores, unless new
                    tappets are used.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Push Rods</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install push rods with the cup end up. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41504.xml" xrefid="e41504">"CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Reinstall the following:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to the appropriate manual section for installation procedures.</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Engine front cover</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Pick-up tube and oil pan</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Water pump</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Water pump pulley</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Oil pump</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Vibration damper and puller</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Injection pump</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Cylinder head</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Push rods</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Rocker arm assembly</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Valve cover</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Thermostat and housing</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Turbocharger</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Intake manifold</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Aneroid tube</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Fuel injection nozzles</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Fuel leak-off lines</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Fuel injection lines</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Crossover pipe</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Crankcase breather tube</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
